Detailed Description

Structure for RTP session.

Note
When RTP redudant payload type is defined, it fills RTP header's payload type field. Original set payload types of TstVoipMgrRtpCfg are used to fill RTP redundant extension header.
SID payload type is used by codec whose timestamp clock rate is not equal to 8000Hz, such as G.722. Its range should be between 96 to 127, and just set it to be 0 in narrowband codec.
